{
  "stem": "18778.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I know it was before Crystal Night, because of the correspondence I'm finding regarding our immigration.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There was, for instance, the dismissal or the deportation of all aliens, Jewish aliens out of Germany in approximately October of 1938 to no man's land between Germany and Poland.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I don't know if it happened before that.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But at one-- some point, I think in 1938, he was convinced it was time to go.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It was time to get out.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I found all kinds of correspondence to that effect.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, first of all, there was Kristallnacht.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And after Kristallnacht, I-- my mother took me to Bonn, to friends who were Dutch nationals, and therefore the house was Dutch property.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And she felt that I would be safe there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And through these friends, my parents met a Cuban family by the name of Stutzel, S-T-U-E-T-Z-E-L.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He was German, but a Cuban-- had become a Cuban citizen.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And his wife was Cuban.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And through their efforts, my parents got these immigration permits into Cuba.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They were visiting Cuba and they heard about it, that the immigration official in Havana was issuing immigration permits.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And they-- they bought them for my parents and brought them back.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And so then, the next step was to find a ways of leaving Germany.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Meanwhile, our relatives in the United States, who up until Crystal Night had felt my father was too old to emigrate into the United States, considering his occupation and his age, had issued us affidavits, which is a guarantee that they would support us in case it was necessary, and so on.",
      "word_count": 52
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And all we needed now was somewhere to go and some way to get there.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
